= Authentication Setup <sup>[[Help:Authentication | <img width="19" src="../images/navigation/help_start.png" />]]</sup>=

Using the following form you can configure the authentication modules and options of the platform. For details on the respective settings, see [[Help:Authentication|Help:Authentication]].

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.admin.AuthenticationConfigurationWidget}}

{{#widget: CodeExecution | 
 passContext = false
 | args = {{ '%username' | '%password' }}
 | userInput = {{ 
      {{ name = 'username'
       | required = true
       | displayName = 'User name'
       | componentType = 'SIMPLE'
      }} | 
      {{ name = 'password'
       | required = false
       | displayName = 'Password'
       | componentType = 'PASSWORD'
      }} }}
 | method = 'testAuthentication'
 | label = 'Test Authentication'
 | clazz = 'com.fluidops.iwb.widget.admin.AuthenticationConfigurationWidget'
}}
<br/>
When authenticating users including the domain part (e.g. ''myuser@mydomain.corp'' instead of just ''myuser''), the ''DIGEST-MD5'' method cannot be used. In this case authentication with plain text passwords needs to be enabled.
<span style="color:red;">Should only be used for LDAPS!</span>
{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.admin.InlineConfigurationWidget | 
 configOptions = {{ 'authenticateLdapUsingPlaintext' | 'authGroupsWithDomain' }}
}}
Additional LDAP related properties:
{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.admin.InlineConfigurationWidget | 
 configOptions = {{ 'ldapFollowReferrals' | 'ldapMaxGroupRecursionDepth' }}
}}